	<Text>The Medal for Valour is awarded for displays of personal courage and valour in the defense of the socialist Homeland and the state frontier of the USSR, and in the execution of military duty involving a risk to life. This medal may be awarded to persons who are not citizens of the USSR.

This decoration was established in October 1938.
</Text>
